parameters: Live2dモーション設定 FR Entry 0 3
\N<Onee-chan>Oh, cute boy. Hello. Are you from this town?
\N<Boku>Yeah, I'm Boku. I live here during summer vacation.

\N<Onee-chan>Oh, Jesse, we're matching. Jesse also comes to
stay at a nearby pension during the summer.
\N<Boku>Huh?! That's my house! Onee-chan, you're a customer.

\N<Onee-chan>Really? That's a coincidence. Then let's get
along well. Please call me Jesse in a friendly manner.
\N<Boku>Yeah, got it! Nice to meet you, Jesse!
\N<Jesse>That's right. Nice to meet you, Boku.
\N<Jesse>Hey, Boku. Did you catch any big fish?
\N<Boku>I caught a catfish! Look, it's big, right?!

\N<Jesse>Wow, a catfish! It's definitely so big. Looks like
I win, huh?

\N<Jesse>Well then, the promised hobby... Ah, sorry. I
haven't thought about it yet.

\N<Jesse>I'll think about it next time. Please look forward
to it.

\N<Jesse>However, do you have any big fish like this? Maybe
Jesse should try fishing in a deeper area too...
\N<Boku>I caught a black bass! See, it's big, right?!

\N<Jesse>Oh, it's definitely big. But it's just a little
smaller than the Carp that Jesse caught.
\N<Boku>Ugh... I need to catch a bigger fish, don't I...
\N<Boku>I caught a carp! See, it's big, right?!

\N<Jesse>Oh, it's definitely big. But it's about the same
size as the Carp that Jesse caught.

\N<Boku>Ugh... I need to catch a bigger fish, don't I...
But, I don't see any around here... Maybe I need to find a
secret fishing spot...

\N<Boku>Come to think of it, didn't Boss-kun tell me about a
secret fishing spot...? Something about catching big fish
only in the evening...?

\N<Boku>I wonder if anyone knows a secret fishing spot...
Boss-kun is older than me, so maybe they know? They might
not tell me in front of everyone, so maybe I should ask when
it's just the two of us...?
\N<Boku>Hey, hey? What are you doing here, Jesse?

\N<Jesse>What a coincidence. Well then, shall we have a
fishing battle, Jesse? Let's see who can catch the biggest
fish in this town!
\N<Boku>Yeah! I won't lose either! I'll catch a huge fish!

\N<Jesse>Well then, if you catch a big fish, please let me
know. If you can beat the fish that Jesse caught, I'll give
you some kind of reward.
\N<Boku>I see... Maybe I should try fishing too...

\N<Jesse>I'll think about the fishing battle event and let
you know next time. Please look forward to it!

\N<Jesse>However, are there really such big fish? Maybe
Jesse should try fishing in the deeper parts too...
ヒメノ湖に最初からいた場合の処理

\N<Boushi-kun>Ouch, ouch. If you don't cook the corn
properly...

\N<\N[2]>Everyone, there's still plenty left, so don't hold
back and eat up!

\N<\N[2]>Oh my, it's fine. I've borrowed the water supply
from Harumi-chan, so it's more fun to have plenty of these
kinds of things.

\N<\N[2]>Well then, Sacchan and the ladies will go home, but
if anything happens, make sure to tell an adult right away.
It's dangerous, so don't go into the lake at night.

\N<Boss-kun>Well then... I'm not sleepy yet, so let's do a
test of courage.

\N<Boss-kun>This is a special training to gather courage as
members of the Hime-no-yama Defense Squad! Everyone is
required to participate!

\N<Boss-kun>The rules are simple! We'll draw lots to
determine pairs, and each pair will go to the three Jizo
statues located to the east of the secret base and come
back!

\N<Boss-kun>Running or pretending to go is not allowed. Well
then, let's determine the pairs right away with a drawing of
lots.
\N<Boku>Um... I'll go with Nana-chan, I guess.

\N<Nana-chan>What's wrong? Do you have any complaints?
Instead, be grateful!

\N<Boku>N-No, I don't have any complaints at all! Yay, I'm
so happy! I can't wait to go!

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, you're enthusiastic, Boku-chan. Well then,
let's start with you and your partner, Boku-chan. Here, we
only have one lantern.
\N<Boku>Gah... Ugh... Being the first one is so...
\N<Boss-kun>Alright, hurry up and go. No cheating, okay?

\N<Boss-kun>Well then, now that the test of courage is over,
I guess it's time to go to sleep.

\N<Boushi-kun>Ugh... Boss-kun, that's terrible... telling
scary stories during the test of courage... I'm too scared
to sleep now...

\N<Boss-kun>Sorry, sorry. Well, it can't be helped. How
about the three of us, me, Boushi, and Hakase, sleep
together? It won't be scary if there are three of us, right?

\N<Boss-kun>Then, Boku-chan and Yuu will be in the middle
tent. Nana will be in the tent on the left.

\N<Boss-kun>There's no one who would risk their life to
peek.
\N<Boss-kun>Oh, scary, scary. Well, let's go to sleep, guys.
\N<Nana-chan>Hey! Don't peek at my perverted stuff, okay?
\N<Yu-kun>Ah, Boku-kun. Shall we go to bed soon?
I'm staying awake for just a little longer
もうちょっとだけ起きてる

\N<Nana-chan>Hey, where are you going? Are you planning to
take me into the tent and do something~?

\N<Boss-kun>What's up? Boku-chan, do you also want to sleep
in this tent? Even if it's just the two of us, it's
impossible to fit four people.

\N<Boss-kun>Alright, Boku-chan. The time has come to show
your manliness!

\N<Boss-kun>Alright, Boku-chan. The time has come to show
your manliness!
\N<Boushi-kun>Ugh... What should I do when it's my turn...
\N<Boushi-kun>Ugh... What should I do when it's my turn...
\N<Yu-kun>Both of you, be careful of your footing.
\N<Yu-kun>Both of you, be careful of your footing.
